				\begin{document}$$ \chi $$\end{document}χ2(2, N = 6) = 6.312, p = 0.043). Additional chi-square-post-hoc revealed that older participants demonstrated a higher frequency of non-MTC gait cycles than the young group (p = 0.039) across conditions; non-MTC gait cycle frequencies were not affected by conditions.
